      REM There are about 6 billion people in the world.  Assuming      REM a growth rate of 1.8% per year, how many people will there      REM be in 100 years?      DIM PEOPLE AS SINGLE :! number of people      DIM YEAR AS INTEGER :! current year      PEOPLE = 6E9      FOR YEAR = 1 TO 10        PEOPLE = PEOPLE * 1.018      NEXT      PRINT "At 1.8% growth, there will be ";PEOPLE;" people in 10 years."